#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:2
msgid "QEMU Barrier Client"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:4
msgid ""
"Generally, mouse and keyboard are grabbed through the QEMU video interface "
"emulation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:7
msgid ""
"But when we want to use a video graphic adapter via a PCI passthrough there "
"is no way to provide the keyboard and mouse inputs to the VM except by "
"plugging a second set of mouse and keyboard to the host or by installing a "
"KVM software in the guest OS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:12
msgid ""
"The QEMU Barrier client avoids this by implementing directly the Barrier "
"protocol into QEMU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:15
msgid ""
"`Barrier <https://github.com/debauchee/barrier>`__ is a KVM (Keyboard-Video-"
"Mouse) software forked from Symless's synergy 1.9 codebase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:19
msgid "This protocol is enabled by adding an input-barrier object to QEMU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:21
msgid "Syntax::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:23
msgid ""
"input-barrier,id=<object-id>,name=<guest display name>\n"
"[,server=<barrier server address>][,port=<barrier server port>]\n"
"[,x-origin=<x-origin>][,y-origin=<y-origin>]\n"
"[,width=<width>][,height=<height>]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:28
msgid "The object can be added on the QEMU command line, for instance with::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:30
msgid "-object input-barrier,id=barrier0,name=VM-1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:32
msgid ""
"where VM-1 is the name the display configured in the Barrier server on the "
"host providing the mouse and the keyboard events."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:35
msgid ""
"by default ``<barrier server address>`` is ``localhost``, ``<port>`` is "
"``24800``, ``<x-origin>`` and ``<y-origin>`` are set to ``0``, ``<width>`` "
"and ``<height>`` to ``1920`` and ``1080``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:39
msgid ""
"If the Barrier server is stopped QEMU needs to be reconnected manually, by "
"removing and re-adding the input-barrier object, for instance with the help "
"of the HMP monitor::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/barrier.rst:43
msgid ""
"(qemu) object_del barrier0\n"
"(qemu) object_add input-barrier,id=barrier0,name=VM-1"
msgstr ""
